  Heat a #medium frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, add the @Riced Cauliflower{250%g}.

Cook until just soft, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Once cooked, cover to keep warm until serving.

Meanwhile, trim the @Green Beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds.

Heat a #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @British Pork Mince{240%g} and green beans, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, in a #bowl{}, mix together the @Peanut Butter{60%g}, @Sweet Chilli Sauce{64%g}, @Soy Sauce{25%ml} and @Boiled Water{125%ml} until smooth.

Add to the pork mince and simmer, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add a splash of water if it's too thick.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Share the cauli rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the satay pork and beans.

Sprinkle over the @Salted Peanuts{25%g}.

Enjoy!